          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConEdisonIsOrignalOrRevisedOnlyBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value, which can be of any SQL data type. This function is designed to determine whether a given billing record is classified as either \"Original\" or \"Revised Only\" billing for ConEdison, a utility company. The function evaluates certain criteria within the billing data to make this determination."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
